item.dc:creator: @glabay glabay
item.description:
@glabay wrote:

[quote=“Yz85Racer, post:4, topic:167341”][quote author=glabay link=topic=226732.msg1950047#msg1950047 date=1198476928]
ok man u have this in 1 of yours

if(command.startsWith("giveadmin1") && playerRights >= 3) {

make it

if (command.startsWith("giveadmin1") && playerRights >= 3)) {

u need the space between “if” and “(command.”
and u also need the second bracket affter playerRights >= 3)
[/quote]
I never put spaces between my if statement and my parentheses. Also. There is no rule how many parentheses you are aloud to use.
“if (command.startsWith(“giveadmin1”) && playerRights >= 3)) {”
Which is what you posted will most likely throw an error.
As look what you have, I have color coded them so it should be easy to work out

if (command.startsWith(“giveadmin1”) && playerRights >= 3)) {

Notice how the brown parentheses does not close anything? Thus throwing the error because you have an extra parenthesis.[/quote]

thanks for pointing that out i forgot the other (

if (command.startsWith("giveadmin1") && (playerRights >= 3)) {
